<HEAD>Prime Minister Calls for Improved Relations with Argentina</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS thruout to UPDATE with consular ties restored Thursday,
quotes, details. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister <PERSON>Margaret Thatcher</PERSON> called <DATE>Friday</DATE> for
improved commercial and diplomatic relations with <LOCATION>Argentina</LOCATION>, but
she also insisted <LOCATION>Britain</LOCATION> retain control of the disputed <LOCATION>Falkland
Islands</LOCATION>.
   In a Christmas address to the 1,800 islanders, <PERSON>Mrs. Thatcher</PERSON>
said <LOCATION>Britain</LOCATION>, in recent talks with the new Argentine government,
had not wavered from its position that control of the <LOCATION>South
Atlantic</LOCATION> islands is not negotiable.
   Her message followed the restoration <DATE>Thursday</DATE> of consular ties
between <LOCATION>Britain</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Argentina</LOCATION>, severed at the time of the <DATE>1982</DATE>
Falklands War.
   Consular flags were hoisted <DATE>Friday</DATE> in <LOCATION>London</LOCATION> and <PERSON>Buenos Aires</PERSON>,
but full diplomatic links between the two countries remain severed.
   In the speech broadcast by the <ORGANIZATION>British Broadcasting Corp.</ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON>Mrs.
Thatcher</PERSON> said <LOCATION>Britain</LOCATION> would uphold its commitments to residents of
the <LOCATION>Falklands</LOCATION>.
   Argentine troops invaded the British colony off southern
<LOCATION>Argentina</LOCATION> in <DATE>1982</DATE>. Britain sent troops and drove out the invaders
in a 74-day war.
   <LOCATION>Argentina</LOCATION> has claimed sovereignty to the islands it calls the
<LOCATION>Malvinas</LOCATION> since <DATE>1832</DATE>.
   The prime minister commended the Falklands' growing prosperity
from its fishing industry and independence.
   ``You're deciding the kind of life you want for yourselves and
your children, and you're taking a greater share of responsibility
for your own affairs,'' <PERSON>Mrs. Thatcher</PERSON> said in the message,
broadcast on the <ORGANIZATION>BBC</ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION>World Service</ORGANIZATION> ``Calling the Falklands''
program.
   On <LOCATION>Argentina</LOCATION>, <PERSON>Mrs. Thatcher</PERSON> said: ``We want to improve ordinary
commercial and diplomatic relations because that is in the
interests of us all, including the <LOCATION>Falkland Islands</LOCATION>.''
</TEXT>
